I'm not familiar with the laws in California, but generally for any form of recorded media to be &quot;admissible&quot; you need direct, not assumed or tacit, consent from the recorded party at the beginning of a conversation.  Likewise, who contacted who is irrelevant.  However legal admissibility and who initiated the contact aren't pertinent to this topic at this time - and let's just hope it never becomes so.<br>
<br>
The relevant issue is that you posted the conversation in an area where you knew and hoped it would get a reaction.  Furthermore, the entire topic revolved around real life issues, not ingame issues.  This wasn't about someone stealing your horse, but rather about someone expressing their misguided, pubescent views on life, and you holding them up for scrutiny and judgement, while fully admitting that you thought Ziderax was a minor:  &quot;Kuladen, I actually believe he's probably 16 or so.&quot;<br>
